ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.function.vector

Class VectorOutputFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.dag.Node
      • ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.function.AtomicFunction
        • ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.function.vector.VectorFunction
          • ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.function.vector.VectorOutputFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Connectable, Contextualizable, ExplanationQueryable, Function, Queryable, Duplicable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParameterizedVectorFunction

    public abstract class VectorOutputFunction
extends VectorFunction
    An atomic function taking as its input a single vector, and producing as its output a single vector (of possibly different size).

    The class extends AtomicFunction by keeping in memory the last pair of input/output lists involved in a function call. It also overrides the explanation provided by its parent AtomicFunction, and provides a boilerplate explanation where:

    • The whole output is explained by the whole input
    • A single element of the output vector is explained by every element of the input vector
    Only vector functions that explain their output differently need to override this method.
    Author:
    Sylvain Hallé
